        {
            "_id": "25v45nqumj44pd4b",
            "data": {
                "actionCategory": {
                    "value": "offensive"
                },
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "action"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": 1
                },
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p><strong>Requirements</strong> The ecorche is holding the stolen skin of a Small, Medium, or Large creature and isn't already wearing a skin;</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> The ecorche wears the skin as a disguise. It assumes the creature's size, appearance, and voice. Wearing Skin counts as creating a disguise for the @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.Impersonate]{Impersonate} use of Deception. The ecorche's transformation automatically defeats Perception DCs to determine whether it's a member of the ancestry or creature type into which it transformed, and the ecorche gains a +4 status bonus to its Deception DC to prevent others from seeing through its disguise.</p>\n<p>Wearing a skin gives the ecorche a +2 item bonus to AC and 75 temporary Hit Points. If the ecorche takes more than [[/r {50}[slashing]]]{50 slashing Damage} from a single source, the skin becomes broken. When broken, the skin no longer provides any of these benefits (any remaining temporary HP are immediately lost) but can still be used for Tear Skin.</p>"
                },
